value.title: Cotton grills Biden Pentagon nominee on 'volatile outbursts,' 'almost always wrong' foreign policy judgments
value.excerpt: Sen. Tom Cotton, R-Ark., accused one of President Biden's top Pentagon picks of having a "long record of volatile outbursts."

value.title: Biden HHS pick refused request to bring humanitarian aid to Cuba on infamous 1996 trip: report
value.excerpt: President Biden’s HHS nominee reportedly refused a request to bring humanitarian aid to Cuba while meeting with Fidel Castro.

value.title: Donald Trump lists oceanfront Palm Beach mansion for $49 million
value.excerpt: A company registered to Donald Trump and his family is selling their Palm Beach oceanfront abode for a whopping $49 million.  The estate sits right next door to Trump’s Mar-a-Lago club,

value.title: Texas border resident blasts Biden's 'truly shameful' immigration policies on 'Fox & Friends'
value.excerpt: Biden’s immigration policies are “truly shameful,” a Texas resident who lives near the border said on Thursday.

value.title: GOP maps out strategy to counter Biden's 'immoral,' 'radical' immigration agenda
value.excerpt: Republicans this week circulated a memo on their plan to counter what they describe as a "radical" and "immoral" immigration agenda from President Biden as the GOP looks to unite against the rolling-back of Trump-era border protections.

value.title: A Pennsylvania man said he would find a local Democratic Party office and "shoot it up" for Donald Trump. And then he did, authorities say.
value.excerpt: Anthony Nero is accused firing his handgun at the Montgomery County Democratic Party's office in Norristown, Pennsylvania.

value.title: Mike Pence breaks silence in op-ed slamming House Dems’ voting reform bill
value.excerpt: Pence made his feelings known in an op-ed published Wednesday by The Daily Signal, a blog run by the conservative Heritage Foundation, where the former VP is a fellow.

value.title: Biden celebrates House passing HR 1, Dems' campaign bill, vows work to 'refine and advance' legislation
value.excerpt: President Biden on Thursday celebrated the House passing a sweeping election reform bill, saying he would sign it if it passes the Senate.

value.title: Rep. Waltz hits back at Biden: Keeping schools closed is 'Neanderthal thinking'
value.excerpt: Rep. Michael Waltz, R-Fla., pushed back on President Biden for calling out red states for lifting mask mandates.

value.title: Once omnipresent Kushner now MIA from Trump's political pack
value.excerpt: As Donald Trump plotted his Conservative Political Action Conference appearance last week, and a broader, more-robust plan to return to politics as an omnipresent disruptor, one person was conspicuously absent from the confab.

value.title: First Thing: Biden slams 'Neanderthal' easing of state Covid restrictions
value.excerpt: Joe Biden strongly criticised states for lifting mask-wearing mandates, as the CDC warned ‘now is not the time’. Plus, Washington security has been ramped up amid possible Capitol attack plans

value.title: Trump election fraud investigation in Georgia enters new phase with grand jury set to be seated
value.excerpt: A criminal investigation into former President Donald Trump's attempts to overturn the 2020 election results in Georgia is set to intensify this week, as a grand jury convenes, offering the local district attorney her first shot at seeking subpoenas for records and interviews.

value.title: Shalanda Young testifies before Senate as top Democrats pressure Biden to pick her for OMB director
value.excerpt: Shalanda Young will testify Thursday morning before the Senate Homeland Security committee, as House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and other top Democrats publicly pressure the Biden administration to pick her to lead the Office of Management and Budget.

value.title: Biden’s US-Mexico border pullback creating ‘roads for the cartels,’ Arizona sheriff says: report
value.excerpt: The U.S.-Mexico border region in Arizona is becoming less secure since President Biden took office, a sheriff is alleging, according to a report.

value.title: Susan Collins says she’ll back Biden pick Deb Haaland for Interior secretary
value.excerpt: U.S. Sen. Susan Collins, R-Maine, said Wednesday that she will vote to confirm U.S. Rep. Deb Haaland of New Mexico to become secretary of the interior.

value.title: Kimmel warns 'canceling' Dr. Seuss is 'how Trump gets reelected': Cancel culture is 'his path to victory'
value.excerpt: ABC late-night host Jimmy Kimmel sounded the alarm on cancel culture Tuesday and how it could help former President Donald Trump get elected again in 2024.

value.title: Georgia Gov. Kemp says he would 'absolutely' back Trump 2024, despite Trumps' calls for his resignation
value.excerpt: Georgia Gov. Brian Kemp said he would "absolutely" back Donald Trump in a bid for the presidency in 2024, despite Trump’s recent criticism of the Republican governor.

value.title: Watchdog asked Trump DOJ to criminally investigate Elaine Chao for misuse of office as transportation secretary but was rebuffed
value.excerpt: The inspector general found that Chao inappropriately used her staff and office for personal tasks and to promote a shipping business owned by Chao’s father and sisters.

value.title: Florida Gov. DeSantis slams Biden over pace of school reopenings: 'Pathetic failure of leadership'
value.excerpt: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis accused President Biden on Sunday of a “pathetic failure of leadership” for the current pace of his nationwide push to reopen schools during the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: Back to school for first lady Jill Biden: There's 'light at end of tunnel' for reopening schools
value.excerpt: First lady Jill Biden and the new education secretary visited schools in Connecticut and Pennsylvania to talk about safely returning to classrooms.

value.title: Fact check: Pence echoes Trump's Big Lie in dishonest op-ed on election rules
value.excerpt: In an opinion article published on Wednesday, former Vice President Mike Pence did something he used to do in office: echo a lie from former President Donald Trump in a slightly more sophisticated way.

value.title: House Republican: 'Trump has a responsibility' to tell his supporters 'to stand down' after new threat
value.excerpt: The top Republican on the House Foreign Affairs Committee said Wednesday that Donald Trump has a duty to call off his supporters in light of a potential threat against the US Capitol on Thursday -- less than two months after the January 6 Capitol insurrection incited by the former President.

value.title: Biden administration singles out China as 'biggest geopolitical test' for U.S
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden singled out a "growing rivalry with China" as a key challenge facing the United States, with his top diplomat describing the Asian country as "the biggest geopolitical test" of this century.

value.title: McConnell blames Biden’s ‘sweeping left-wing amnesty plan' for fueling border surge
value.excerpt: Senate GOP Leader Mitch McConnell on Wednesday blamed President Biden’s “sweeping left-wing amnesty plan” for fueling the escalating migrant crisis on the southern border -- and said it sidelined the interests of American workers.

value.title: Biden criticizes Texas and Mississippi for lifting restrictions: 'Neanderthal thinking'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden sharply criticized states such as Texas and Mississippi for lifting Covid-19 restrictions against pleas from the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and other top public health officials, accusing those in power of "Neanderthal thinking."
